laboratory_examinations.findings: Uterine cavity had normal volume, symmetric contours, no mucosal irregularity or filling defects. Proximal fallopian tubes filled promptly and were of normal caliber, but distal ampullary and infundibular portions were abnormally dilated with multiple filling defects. Lack of free spillage of contrast material indicated bilateral tubal occlusion.
